00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:46.099
But I found Earl Jenkins hiding in the loft.

00:15:46.179 --> 00:15:47.120
He was looking for you, Dad.

00:15:47.839 --> 00:15:48.740
He's all messed up.

00:15:49.919 --> 00:15:50.860
What's the matter with Earl?

00:15:51.319 --> 00:15:52.659
I don't know, but he's wanted for murder.

00:15:54.059 --> 00:15:54.500
Earl?

00:15:56.419 --> 00:15:57.860
What did he have to say for himself?

00:15:57.860 --> 00:15:58.879
I couldn't get close.

00:15:59.159 --> 00:15:59.980
How come? The police?

00:16:00.320 --> 00:16:04.360
No, because when I got near him, I got sick.

00:16:05.259 --> 00:16:06.259
It was weird.

00:16:06.860 --> 00:16:09.340
I mean, every time I stood next to him, it got worse.

00:16:09.399 --> 00:16:11.600
It's kind of like...

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:13.060
Like what?

00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:18.180
It's kind of like the way I feel around meteor fragments.

00:16:27.860 --> 00:16:32.519
What's wrong with him?

00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:36.620
Well, to be honest, I haven't the faintest idea.

00:16:37.840 --> 00:16:40.460
It's amazing his body's been able to survive the seizures this long.

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:44.279
Here, take a look at the x-rays.

00:16:47.379 --> 00:16:49.440
It looks like he's got some sort of mineral poisoning,

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:51.200
but it's not the mini-mineral I've seen before.

00:16:51.519 --> 00:16:52.620
Is that why he's shaking so hard?

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:55.180
Tiny fragments of the mineral are embedded under his skin.

00:16:55.279 --> 00:16:57.060
His body is slowly trying to push them out.

00:16:57.860 --> 00:17:01.860
He claims there was an explosion at the Luther Corps plant six months ago.

00:17:01.860 --> 00:17:03.860
I don't remember hearing anything about that.

00:17:03.860 --> 00:17:05.860
That's because it didn't happen.

00:17:05.860 --> 00:17:09.860
I pulled the plant's safety records, I checked with OSHA and the EPA.

00:17:12.860 --> 00:17:14.860
Doc, can I go in and talk to him by myself?

00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:19.860
Better hurry up. Metropolis PD will be here any minute to transfer him back to the city.

00:17:19.860 --> 00:17:20.860
Thanks.

00:17:22.860 --> 00:17:23.860
I want to go with you.

00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:24.860
No.

00:17:24.859 --> 00:17:28.859
Listen, you said that you felt sick when you got around him, right?

00:17:28.859 --> 00:17:32.859
Now I'm guessing that whatever he was exposed to has got something to do with those meteor rocks,

00:17:32.859 --> 00:17:34.859
and I don't want you passing out around here.

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:37.859
That'd bring us a whole other set of problems.

00:17:45.859 --> 00:17:47.859
Jonathan.

00:17:47.859 --> 00:17:50.859
Am I glad to see you.

00:17:50.859 --> 00:17:52.859
Hey, look.

00:17:54.859 --> 00:17:55.859
It's over.

00:17:55.859 --> 00:17:57.859
minds lose their own loses their own

00:17:57.859 --> 00:17:59.859
parts like an elderly person

00:17:59.859 --> 00:18:02.859
Clark, I hear you?

00:18:05.859 --> 00:18:09.859
But some beaters said that you could be dead already.

00:18:09.859 --> 00:18:11.859
Come on, will ya?

00:18:11.859 --> 00:18:12.859
Can I not?

00:18:16.859 --> 00:18:17.859
Chip.

00:18:17.859 --> 00:18:18.859
Yeah.

00:18:19.859 --> 00:18:21.859
Who the fuck's in danger?

00:18:21.859 --> 00:18:25.359
I was trying to see Lionel Luther.

00:18:25.359 --> 00:18:26.179
Why?

00:18:26.179 --> 00:18:30.559
Find out what they were using on level three.

00:18:30.559 --> 00:18:33.919
Earl, you're not making any sense.

00:18:33.919 --> 00:18:36.879
When I got that job at the Smallville plant,

00:18:36.879 --> 00:18:39.679
I was assigned to clean level three.

00:18:39.679 --> 00:18:43.339
I'm doing these hush-hush crop experiments.

00:18:43.339 --> 00:18:44.959
The new kind of fertilizer's supposed to make

00:18:44.959 --> 00:18:47.899
corn grow twice as fast.

00:18:47.899 --> 00:18:50.859
There was something in that fertilizer that was unstable.

00:18:50.859 --> 00:18:52.299
It was a huge explosion.

00:18:52.299 --> 00:18:54.039
I was cleaning at the time.

00:18:54.039 --> 00:18:57.639
And the stuff, it got under my skin.

00:18:57.639 --> 00:19:01.279
The next thing I know, they shut it all down,

00:19:01.279 --> 00:19:03.879
and I was transferred to Metropolis.

00:19:03.879 --> 00:19:08.299
Then two months ago, the jitters started.

00:19:08.299 --> 00:19:09.639
Did you see a doctor?

00:19:09.639 --> 00:19:13.479
I must have seen 50, but nobody could tell me what was wrong.

00:19:13.479 --> 00:19:16.099
They needed to know what I was exposed to.

00:19:16.099 --> 00:19:17.919
But when I went back to the plant,

00:19:17.919 --> 00:19:20.639
they told me that level three didn't exist.

00:19:20.859 --> 00:19:23.199
That it never had.

00:19:23.199 --> 00:19:25.899
I got to find out what they were using.

00:19:25.899 --> 00:19:27.979
That's why I need your help.

00:19:27.979 --> 00:19:30.240
You've got to get me out of here.

00:19:30.240 --> 00:19:32.740
Earl, you're wanted for murder.

00:19:32.740 --> 00:19:34.619
Oh, you don't understand.

00:19:34.619 --> 00:19:35.619
I can't control it.

00:19:35.619 --> 00:19:37.059
I'm running out of time.

00:19:37.059 --> 00:19:39.259
The jitters are getting worse.

00:19:39.259 --> 00:19:44.679
It's already cost me my job, my marriage, my baby.

00:19:44.679 --> 00:19:47.439
I got to get back into that plant, or I'm going to die.

00:19:50.859 --> 00:19:51.859
Help me.

00:19:56.740 --> 00:19:58.240
You get some rest, Earl.

00:20:06.459 --> 00:20:08.059
Do you think he's telling the truth?

00:20:08.059 --> 00:20:10.619
I have no idea.

00:20:10.619 --> 00:20:12.500
Yeah, I've got a field trip to the movable core

00:20:12.500 --> 00:20:13.399
plant this afternoon.

00:20:13.399 --> 00:20:14.459
Maybe I can take a look around.

00:20:14.459 --> 00:20:16.319
I know that you're worried about Earl,

00:20:16.319 --> 00:20:18.099
but he's got more trouble than he can handle.

00:20:18.099 --> 00:20:19.839
And I know this is right, Mike, so please don't, don't worry.

00:20:19.839 --> 00:20:20.779
Okay.

00:20:20.859 --> 00:20:22.859
I won't do anything.

00:20:45.859 --> 00:20:47.859
Mommy, I don't want to go to the doctors.

00:20:47.859 --> 00:20:49.859
They're gonna give me a shot.

00:20:49.859 --> 00:20:51.859
I thought you said last time.

00:20:53.859 --> 00:20:55.859
Mommy!

00:21:10.859 --> 00:21:14.859
Hello, everybody. I'm Gabe Sullivan, plant manager and proud father.

00:21:14.859 --> 00:21:15.859
Hi, sweetheart.

00:21:15.859 --> 00:21:16.859
Hi, dad.

00:21:16.859 --> 00:21:18.859
Welcome to Luther Corp.

00:21:18.859 --> 00:21:20.859
Where we give a crap.

00:21:20.859 --> 00:21:22.859
Okay, somebody kill me now.

00:21:22.859 --> 00:21:24.859
A little fertilizer humor there.

00:21:24.859 --> 00:21:29.859
All right, before we go inside, I need you to remove all your cell phones, pagers, jewelry,

00:21:29.859 --> 00:21:33.859
anything that jangles, dangles, or rings has to go on these plastic trays right here.

00:21:33.859 --> 00:21:35.859
All right? Any other questions?

00:21:35.859 --> 00:21:36.859
Yes?

00:21:36.859 --> 00:21:38.859
I heard there was a third level to the plant. Is that true?

00:21:39.859 --> 00:21:42.859
Yeah. Yeah. That's where we do the alien autopsies.

00:21:43.859 --> 00:21:45.859
I think we better get started.

00:21:45.859 --> 00:21:46.859
Don't encourage him.

00:21:46.859 --> 00:21:47.859
This way, everybody.

00:21:48.859 --> 00:21:50.859
All right, people. Let's stay together.

